## Interpretation Notes

- The primary quality signal is executable task success, not text similarity.
- `agent_failures` usually indicate CLI/auth/runtime issues. `verify_failures` mean the agent completed but the produced patch failed the task verifier.
- Run at least several tasks and repeats before drawing procurement or production conclusions.
- Subscription-backed agents can be good baselines for coding quality, but they do not expose the same token, model metadata, and transport evidence as API runs.
